</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Barnes &amp; McDunnough" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[315,489,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[315,489,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Hypotrix spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially looks like a brown, well-marked form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallela">
<emphasis box="[1078,1100,1435,1460]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[140,230,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">parallela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but averages slightly larger (forewing length: 
<quantity box="[734,862,1469,1496]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="13.0">13–15 mm</quantity>
), the reniform and orbicular spots are larger and outlined by a contrasting pale line, the reniform spot is more rectangular, and spiniform setae are on all three pairs of tibiae. The 
<emphasis box="[872,1020,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">male genitalia</emphasis>
also are very different from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[452,578,1575,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallela">
<emphasis box="[452,474,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[488,578,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">parallela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the uncus is slender with an abruptly spatulate apex, the cucullis is longer and narrower, and the vesica lacks subbasal cornuti, is more tightly coiled medially, and has a field of minute spines postmedially. In the 
<emphasis box="[980,1107,1645,1671]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">female geni-</emphasis>
</paragraph>
