<emphasis box="[140,188,1223,1249]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="237">talia</emphasis>
the corpus bursae is smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lafontaine &amp; Ferris &amp; Walsh" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Grote" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[646,773,1223,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hypotrix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parallela">
